{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6692b3db-061d-4927-8471-31fd7c2bb93b","content":"","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01My8WAHNKQF8tEBbdKD7rYE","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Providing crash dump config"},"type":"function"}],"interactionId":"48a71566-9141-43f5-a4dd-7f0a5114480d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to configure automatic crash dump collection for a NativeAOT .NET 11 app running in Kubernetes. They have `createdump` installed at `/opt/tools/createdump`. Let me provide the environment variable configuration and Kubernetes pod spec changes needed.\n\nFor .NET crash dump collection, the key environment variables are:\n- `DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump` = `1` (enable crash dumps)\n- `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType` = `1` (Mini), `2` (Heap), `3` (Triage), `4` (Full)\n\n\n- `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName` = path template for dump files\n- `DOTNET_CreateDumpDiagnostics` = `1` (optional, for debugging dump creation)\n\nFor NativeAOT specifically, I need to set `DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath` to point to the `createdump` tool location at `/opt/tools/createdump`, since NativeAOT uses the same environment variables but requires the explicit path to the tool. Now I'll work through the pod spec changes needed.","outputTokens":360,"requestId":"1B85:1007E7:160716E:18B6E9A:6A028691"},"id":"f96d97a0-3c56-4677-853e-da22dc9946b8","timestamp":"2026-05-12T01:47:07.117Z","parentId":"61e3f062-6b2c-4ba3-b574-845cbec95824"}
