{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"9e5df6ed-6a86-4173-8fc0-a8f57b99f7d2","content":"Here's what you need:\n\n**Environment variables** for your container spec:\n\n```yaml\nenv:\n  # Enable crash dumps on unhandled exceptions/crashes\n  - name: DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump\n    value: \"1\"\n  # Dump type: 1=Mini, 2=Heap, 3=Triage, 4=Full\n  - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType\n    value: \"4\"\n  # Path to createdump (required for NativeAOT)\n  - name: DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath\n    value: \"/opt/tools/createdump\"\n  # Dump output path (%d = PID, %t = timestamp)\n  - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName\n    value: \"/tmp/dumps/coredump.%d.%t.dmp\"\n```\n\n**Pod spec changes** — add an `emptyDir` volume so dumps survive container restarts and can be retrieved:\n\n```yaml\nspec:\n  containers:\n    - name: your-app\n      # ... your existing container config ...\n      env:\n        - name: DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump\n          value: \"1\"\n        - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType\n          value: \"4\"\n        - name: DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath\n          value: \"/opt/tools/createdump\"\n        - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName\n          value: \"/tmp/dumps/coredump.%d.%t.dmp\"\n      volumeMounts:\n        - name: crash-dumps\n          mountPath: /tmp/dumps\n  volumes:\n    - name: crash-dumps\n      emptyDir:\n        sizeLimit: 2Gi\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- **`DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath`** is required for NativeAOT since there's no runtime-bundled `createdump`.\n- Use **type `4` (Full)** for NativeAOT — you'll want the full memory for debugging without managed heap metadata.\n- The `emptyDir` volume persists dumps across container restarts within the same pod. For durable storage, swap to a `PersistentVolumeClaim`.\n- Retrieve dumps with: `kubectl cp <pod>:/tmp/dumps ./dumps`","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"48a71566-9141-43f5-a4dd-7f0a5114480d","outputTokens":574,"requestId":"1B85:1007E7:160966A:18B9832:6A02869A"},"id":"33648712-6f66-4659-a0e0-80080c25d60e","timestamp":"2026-05-12T01:47:17.628Z","parentId":"154b90e5-2b0e-4adb-90a8-820804718447"}
